  "text": "In the first subsection we review the shifting technique for gradient maps which translates the problem of finding an open Q 0 -orbit in X into the problem of finding an open G-orbit in the bigger gradient manifold X × (K/M ). Since G is real-reductive, we may apply the techniques developed in [CITATION_1] to solve the second problem.",
